368
00:50:35,440 --> 00:50:36,941
...and you love beautiful clothes.

369
00:50:37,141 --> 00:50:39,710
Thanks a lot.
And you dress her because...

370
00:50:39,910 --> 00:50:44,114
She was a good customer and you didn't
want her to be embarrassed.

371
00:50:44,648 --> 00:50:48,452
She had a 0.21 blood alcohol level,
not that that makes any difference.

372
00:50:48,619 --> 00:50:50,119
She didn't drive.

373
00:50:50,319 --> 00:50:53,789
The chauffeurs, they keep
exact mileage on these cars.

374
00:50:53,990 --> 00:50:56,959
They haven't been driven
since the clan left town.

375
00:50:57,159 --> 00:51:00,029
I checked every cab and limo service.
No one knows a thing.

376
00:51:00,096 --> 00:51:02,230
Somebody drove her home. Who?

377
00:51:02,831 --> 00:51:05,267
- Why haven't they come forward?
- Maybe...

378
00:51:05,433 --> 00:51:07,669
...because whoever drove her home
killed her.

379
00:51:10,205 --> 00:51:11,138
Maybe.

380
00:51:11,605 --> 00:51:13,140
I love this case.

381
00:51:13,440 --> 00:51:14,642
Lieutenant?

382
00:51:14,842 --> 00:51:17,311
The problems you had with the phones?

383
00:51:17,778 --> 00:51:19,813
- Just took care of them.
- Thank you.

384
00:51:20,614 --> 00:51:22,248
Just part of the job.

385
00:51:22,849 --> 00:51:25,084
I hate people who say that.

386
00:51:25,285 --> 00:51:27,086
It is your fucking job.

387
00:51:27,620 --> 00:51:29,589
Remember the bullet hole in the wall?

388
00:51:29,789 --> 00:51:31,124
Guess what?

389
00:51:31,291 --> 00:51:32,258
No slug.

390
00:51:32,325 --> 00:51:36,194
